# Paragraph subsection naming (ASME B31.3 pack)

When creating or editing paragraph nodes under `knowledge/standards/asme/asme_b31.3/nodes/paragraph/`:

## Node identity

| Field | Rule | Example |
| --- | --- | --- |
| `id` / filename | `{section}-{lowercase_letter}` | `304.1.2-a`, `302.3.5-e` |
| `paragraph_number` | Same as `id` (hyphen form) | `304.1.2-a` — **not** `304.1.2(a)` |
| `key` | Underscore machine key | `b313_304_1_2_a` |
| Pack prefix | Bare ids (no `B313-` prefix) | `304.1.1-a` |

## Edge targets

Point `edges[].target` at the subsection **node id** (e.g. `302.3.5-e`). Do not use slash notation (`302.3.5/e`) once the subsection is a separate node.

## Prose vs identity

- `text.original` may keep official standard citation style with parentheses: `**(a)**`.
- Graph ids and `paragraph_number` always use the hyphen form.

## Unlettered paragraphs

- No lettered subsections → single unsuffixed id (`304.1.3`).
- Preamble before first lettered subsection → keep unsuffixed base id (`304.3.1`) with children `304.3.1-b`, `304.3.1-c`, etc. Do not invent `304.3.1-a` when the standard has no subsection (a).

## Hierarchy vs `related_to`

| Use | Where |
| --- | --- |
| Parent, children, sibling order | `hierarchy.parent`, ordered `hierarchy.children` on parent nodes |
| Cross-paragraph citation in `text.original` | `related_to` edge only (e.g. text cites para. 302.3.5(e) → `related_to: 302.3.5-e`) |

Do **not** author `hierarchy.previous` or `hierarchy.next`. Workflow sequencing uses workflow `next` edges.

Do **not** author a `links` metadata block — use typed `edges` only (see [`audits/contracts/nodes/01-shared-node-contract.md`](../../audits/contracts/nodes/01-shared-node-contract.md)).

Do **not** use `related_to` for parent/child structure. Do **not** author `parent`, `child`, `next`, or `previous` in paragraph `edges` — use `hierarchy` metadata only.

Full rule: [`audits/contracts/nodes/paragraph.md`](../../audits/contracts/nodes/paragraph.md).

## Revision metadata (required)

```yaml
metadata:
  last_revision: 2026-07-04   # ISO date
  edited_by: admin
```

Pack-level `source_language` lives in `pack.yaml` at the pack root (inherited by all nodes). Do not set `text.source_language` on paragraph nodes.

Nomenclature paragraphs (`metadata.kind: nomenclature`, e.g. `304.1.1-b`): only `introduces_parameter` edges — tables belong on `PARAM-*` nodes.

Full template: [`audits/contracts/nodes/paragraph.md`](../../audits/contracts/nodes/paragraph.md).
